postcontent:
I have for sale/trade a kinda rarish Russian SKS, it's what is known as a "Letter Gun" or "Letter Series" SKS, it is basically one of the last SKS's that was made by Russia, many sources vary on exactly when these were produced, some say 1955-1957, but these were the last made before the switch over to the AK.

When I got it it had a crappy tapco stock on it and an aftermarket receiver cover scope mount, I fit it into a Norinco stock that I refinished, with a standard receiver cover. I am including all the ammo I have for it which is 280 rounds, 180 rounds is still in boxes, 100 is on 10 round stripper clips. title: For Sale:  Glock 23 Gen 4 + 9mm Conversion Barrel, 3 mags + case + guide rod laser
postcontent:
Glock 23, gen 4 in .40SW for sale. I also have a 9mm drop in conversion barrel that allows you to shoot 9mm out of this gun as well. I've put nearly 350 rounds of 9mm downrange with it with zero issues. You will need 9mm glock mags for that.

The gun has been pretty flawless, but I want to move to a 1911. There is a tiny bit of holster wear on the front of the slide, it's very minimal and it will happen with any gun which is placed into and removed from a holster.

I have also added an american flag slide backplate on here, but still have the original glock one if you want a more sterile look. I also have an extra magazine release (that's never been installed), and an extended slide release lever that I used for a while. I also have the original interchangeable backstraps that can be added to the back of the grip to get a custom fit. All of these parts are very easy to swap out and can be done in a matter of minutes.

I also have a lasermax guide-rod laser for it, which I've only used once at the range. It's a pretty neat gizmo, and very easy to put in/take out. It replaces the factory recoil spring, with one which incorporates a laser module into it, providing you with a laser sight that goes nearly exactly where the point of impact will be. I have an extra set of batteries for that as well.

I'm asking $650, OR a reasonable trade for a decent 1911. Worst I can say is no, but please- no low balls. VT residents, 21+ and must be willing to sign a bill of sale.
